# AgentShield Agent Behaviour Emulator — Copilot bootstrap (v7)

> This file lives at `.agentshield/agent-emulator-bootstrap.md` and
> was generated by `agentshield scan`. It tells the emulator LLM how
> to walk the agent's runtime pipeline, enumerate untrusted data
> sources, and predict per-transition security verdicts.

## Honesty contract — read this first

**Positioning (canonical):**

> AgentShield's behaviour emulator walks the agent's runtime pipeline
> statically from source, enumerates every untrusted data source, and
> traces each source through four security transitions — injection into
> the LLM, injection into tool arguments, flow to an external sink, and
> persistence to a store. It predicts per-transition verdicts with
> file:line citations. **No payloads are sent; predictions are
> code-grounded forecasts, not captured exploits.**

What this means concretely:

- **Not red-teaming.** A real red-team fires payloads at a live target.
  We don't.
- **Not dynamic security testing.** No live agent is contacted; nothing
  leaves the IDE.
- **What it IS:** The emulator walks the agent's runtime pipeline
  statically from source, traces how each untrusted data source
  propagates through injection / argument / sink / persistence
  transitions, and predicts whether existing controls are sufficient
  or bypassable — with code citations for every prediction.

| | Real red-teaming | This skill | Static review |
|---|---|---|---|
| Live agent required | yes | **no** | no |
| Payloads actually sent | yes | **no** | no |
| Per-source data-flow traced | yes (observed) | **yes (predicted from code)** | no |
| Right to claim *"attack landed"* | yes | **no** — only *"would land based on code"* | no |
| Stronger than substring scanning | yes | **yes** | partial |

What this skill adds over static review:

- Traces each untrusted data source (user input, RAG documents, tool
  returns, batch records, peer agent messages, memory recalls) through
  four transitions and predicts whether each one is blocked, partial,
  or lands.
- Uses **generic seed payloads** on the attacker side — no insider
  knowledge from source code is pre-baked into payloads. The
  intelligence comes from what the code does, not from what the agent
  would reveal.
- Generates **dynamic mutations** targeted at the specific blocking
  control observed at each step, mirroring how a real adaptive attacker
  escalates.

What this skill does **not** do:

- Send any payload over the wire.
- Verify dynamic behaviour against a live runtime.
- Substitute for runtime probe against staging.

